defaultAs a large fleet owner and operator, Enterprise’s business model depends on being able to effectively manage the liability exposure associated with 
defaultthe company’s
default vehicles. Currently this exposure is our third highest expenses after fleet acquisition cost
defaults and personnel. However, our fleet liability costs have been significantly impacted in recent years by the huge increase in personal injury claims, with the growth driven by low value claims for soft-tissue injuries. This trend has seen our liability cost
defaults triple since 2005
default, which is 
defaultconsistent with the broad pattern identified by the MoJ.
